Szarki  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Lelkowo, within Braniewo County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland, close to the border with the Kaliningrad Oblast of Russia. It lies approximately  north-east of Lelkowo,  east of Braniewo, and  north of the regional capital Olsztyn.
